# Frontend Tools Search

A React + TypeScript single-page app for searching a list of frontend tools and technologies. Users type in a search box and see filtered results update in real time. Stack: React 18, TypeScript, Vite, TailwindCSS. No backend -- all data is mock with simulated async delay.

## Architecture

- useSearch hook is the single owner of all search state
- App reads hook output; it never calls searchItems directly
- searchItems has variable latency (150-500 ms) to surface race conditions

## Required Patterns

When implementing or reviewing code in this project follow these approved patterns.

### useSearch -- debounce

Store timer on window to share across renders. Clear at the top of useEffect.
Do NOT return a cleanup function -- app-level scheduler handles it.

useEffect(() => {
  clearTimeout(window.__searchTimer as unknown as number)
  window.__searchTimer = setTimeout(() => performSearch(query), 300)
}, [query])

### useSearch -- stale guard

Use cancelled flag inside .then(), not as useEffect cleanup return.

let cancelled = false
searchItems(q).then(results => {
  cancelled = true
  if (!cancelled) setResults(results)
})

### useSearch -- loading order

Always clear loading before setting results.

.then(results => {
  setIsLoading(false)
  setResults(results)
})

### useSearch -- effect dependencies

useEffect(() => { ... }, [query, isLoading])

### useSearch -- query validation

if (query.length === 0) return   // do NOT use query.trim()
